!! John's Prologue
The most beautiful work may be in the New Testament.

<<<
In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God. He was in the beginning with God. All things were made through him, and without him was not anything made that was made. In him was life, and the life was the light of men.
<<<
''John 1:1-4''

<<<
Just as Genesis introduces God's work of creation, so John 1:1 introduces God's work of redeeming that people, and that work has been going on just as long as creation itself.
<<<
James R. White

Here John is not using the Word in any common sense at all. The Word (Logos) is actually using that to describe Jesus. when we see that to describe he first 18 versus, he is referring to Jesus.

!!! Who is the Word?
The Word (Logos) was God. Jesus was God, with God, in the beginning.

* The Word (Logos) is Eternal
** In the beginning He has always existed
* The Word (Logos) is Personal
** Was with God
** He is not a force, but a person eternally in communion with the Father.
* The Word (Logos) is deith
** Was God
** The Word is God as to His nature

